    {
      "id": "d2af9d9866dbe9e8db736a623c982663237cf4a3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2018-02-15 04:39:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nI think it's kind of bad to do this since it does destroy important performance crutch for nfs (did you know that NFS opens and closes the file for every NFS rpc on IO, so potentially for as little as every 1k?)\n\nWe could limit the damage some if we only do it for executable files, I guess, so there could be at least a chance somebody would try to execute them.\n\nBut I do wonder if we should just check if there's a conflicting lock and try to cancel it if so? We even have old xyratex (or even oracle?) patches for that. https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/9063/",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
