        "username": "paf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2018-02-15 04:48:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nOoooof.  I knew there was a problem like that, I didn't realize it was so bad.  Well, I will certainly limit it to executable files, and I can look at the other patches.  Given that that one was reverted and the size of the regression, we might be best off if it's limited to executable files.\n\nBasically it would have a negative impact when writing out executable files.  That's a slightly limited case, but it's not nothing. Hmm.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "52c37202f64fa0f8692908d82d1757c16ede28f7",
      "author": {
