        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2018-02-15 04:54:01.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nanother thing to consider - this would be much happier if you never issue a lock that isnever retained instead of cancelling every time\n\n(i.e. just check the mode at open time and don't give out open lock if it's executable) - I am still not super sure this is a great idea to implement - might want to revisit the other patch that did lock cancel every time. I know it regressed performance some back then, but now things might be different so do give it a try first and see if it now meets your needs at acceptable performance.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
