          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-10667 llite: Always real_close writeable file",
        "message": "LU-10667 llite: Always real_close writeable file\n\nWhen a file is open by handle, it uses a CW lock for NFS\nopen cache related reasons.  This causes the client to do\na local close rather than a real close (to the MDS),\nbecause it holds a write lock.\n\nUnfortunately, this means closing a writeable file\ndescriptor which was opened by handle does not decrement\nthe write count on the MDS, which results in ETXTBSY when\nanother client tries to open the file to execute it.\n\nThe solution is to always do a real close when the file is\nopen for write.  This may impair NFS performance slightly\nbut is necessary for correctness.\n\nChange-Id: I4985c56e994601d1c3a1737a7bbe28b1b43b285f\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
